Copy TEAM Mentor files to local folder



              Download&nbsp;the .zip file of TEAM Mentor and extract it


            You can also do a 
Git Clone of the latest version of TEAM Mentor from GitHub (see Install TEAM Mentor from a GitHub Repository)





          The&nbsp;


          TEAM Mentor root folder should contain the following folders:&nbsp;

        Docs
        Tools
        Web Applications
        Library_Data (Note: Only the zip file will have this directory, for TM cloned from GitHub this directory will automatically be created on first run of TM)



          Add TEAM Mentor to IIS 6.0. Open the "Internet Information Services (IIS) Manager".&nbsp;


            Navigate to "Web Sites" in the tree on the left of the "Internet Information Services (IIS) &nbsp;
            Manager" window.&nbsp;


            Right-click on "Web Sites" and select "New" -> "Web Site...”&nbsp;


            A&nbsp;
            "Web Site Creation Wizard" should appear.&nbsp;


            Click "Next".&nbsp;


            Enter a description for the web&nbsp;
            site, something like "TEAM Mentor".&nbsp;


            Click "Next".&nbsp;


            Change the port setting, if necessary.&nbsp;


            Click "Next".&nbsp;


            Click "Browse...”&nbsp;


            Select to the "Web Applications\TM_Website" folder&nbsp;
            inside the TEAM Mentor root folder&nbsp;


            Click "Next".&nbsp;


            Check&nbsp;
            the checkbox next to "Run scripts (such as ASP)".&nbsp;


            Click "Next".&nbsp;


            Click "Finish". 
A new&nbsp;
            web site should appear in the tree structure on the left of the "Internet Information&nbsp;
            Services (IIS) Manager" window.&nbsp;


            Right-click on this new web site.&nbsp;


            Select "Properties". A&nbsp;
            "Properties" window should appear.&nbsp;


            Go to the "ASP.NET" tab in the "Properties"&nbsp;
            window.&nbsp;


            Set the .NET version to 4.0. Click "OK". 








        Set up SSL. SSL is enabled by default for TEAM Mentor. Therefore it is necessary to set up SSL certificate. (Note: It is possible to disable SSL configuration see: )

        First generate a CSR






            Right-click on the newly created web site.&nbsp;


            Select "Properties". A&nbsp;
            "Properties" window should appear. 


            Click on the Directory Security tab, and hit the Server Certificate button.


            Follow the Wizzard to create the CSR


            Send the CSR to your Certificate Authority for Signing







Install your certificate

          Right-Click on the website that the CSR was created on and select Properties.&nbsp;
          Go to the Directory Security panel. Click on the "Server Certificate..." button. This will start the certificate wizard. Click "Next
          Choose to Process the pending request and install the certificate and click Next.
          "Browse" for your SSL Certificate file received from the Certificate Authority, then Click Next. Follow the rest of the wizard steps until finished.




          Set up Permissions, the account used by IIS needs to have write privileges to the TEAM Mentor Library_Data folder



              Identify the application account. which is the Windows user account used by the&nbsp;
            IIS Application Pool configured on the TEAM Mentor
 website.


                On the "Internet&nbsp;
                Information Services (IIS) Manager".&nbsp;


                Navigate to "Application Pools" in the tree on the&nbsp;
                left.&nbsp;


                Right-click on the "Default App Pool" and select "Properties". A "Properties"&nbsp;
                window should appear.&nbsp;


                Go to the "Identity" tab in the "Properties" window. Take note of&nbsp;
                the selected user-name. By default, it is "Network Service".





              Adjust the file-system permissions. Give write permissions for the TEAM Mentor Library_Data folder&nbsp;
            to the Windows user account that is used
 to run TEAM Mentor. This is the username that&nbsp;
            has been discovered in the previous step.&nbsp;


                Right click on the TEAM Mentor Library_Data folder


                Select "Properties". A "Properties" window&nbsp;
                should appear.&nbsp;


                Select the "Security" tab in the "Properties" window. Give "Full Access"&nbsp;
                permissions to the Windows account that is used to run TEAM Mentor.&nbsp;


                Click "OK"

